and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=336005">Lagspike</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> too.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=palaxis@thesaryrntavern>Palaxis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(12/2/03 11:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3716.topic&index=177>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This whole debate is silly. Some people like to be handed loot to them on a silver platter. Some prefere to work for it. It's obvious that those who like to work for it wont say congrats to those who prefere to get it for &quot;free&quot;, so don't expect it. Personally, I would much rather be working my way through NToV than cheat, but that's just me.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm not going to argue about the &quot;spoonfeeding&quot; of information or claim that we figured everything out on our own, because it would be fruitless, and of course we went in with a working idea of the fight's generalities. Several people will never believe that we could fight our way out of a paper bag without being told which end was open, but as someone who has played part of the role in determining our healing strategies, I can honestly tell you, and not feel guilty saying it, that we figure most of that aspect (I'm not so much involved with other aspects, like pulling, tanking, positioning, etc., so I won't speak for them) out ourselves, with little extra info to go by. I don't expect everyone to be happy for what we've accomplished, because there will always be the doubters that believe that we were handed all the knowledge we have, despite not having firsthand experience themselves. However, what you believe to be true does not have to directly correspond to what I have experienced. We will all believe what we want, and arguing the semantics and our &quot;views&quot; of how things really happen won't really do anyone any good.<br>
<br>
We <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>are</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> working for our loot, at least I think so. Statements like the one quoted above are the ones some of us will take issue with, because it blatantly calls us cheaters, and implies that we can't and don't figure things out on our own. We <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">don't</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> prefer to get it for &quot;free&quot;, and for that reason, we're <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">not</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> getting it for &quot;free&quot;, though you can believe what you choose to believe. We do plenty of learning and figuring out on our attempts, even if we do go into the encounter with a general knowledge (not a complete spoiler or a list of details to watch for) of what to expect. There are many many people in ToN who are involved in the decision making process in a raid, not just 3 ex-HnE members, not just Raevan, not just anyone. I don't think we're &quot;stealing strategies&quot; from TJ or HnE or anyone else. I know rae does a lot of scouting yes, to the point of obsession, and I assume he must have some method of doing so, since he's a pally and they don't track. I also know he's obsessive about tracking, and his presence in PoEB may have just been him sitting there and hoping TJ would wipe so that it would be available for us to try, though I can't say for sure, since I'm not him. I do sincerely hope we're not using information obtained in this manner from other guilds successes, because personally I don't agree with it. If indeed we are, I'm gonna be really bummed. Figuring out where to put people and how many people we need to allocate for one task and how to overcome the other obstacles is the only part of the progression process that I really enjoy anymore.<br>
<br>
I've used the word &quot;we&quot; a lot in this post, but I want to emphasize these are my thoughts and mine alone. I speak for no one and no ones experiences but my own. I know what work I've done to help us progress, and I'm proud of what I've put in and what part I have played in assisting ToN's progression. I hope all of my guildmates can confidently say the same with a clear conscience. It's on the shoulders of the individual if they can not.<br>
<br>
Palaxis<br>
65 Cleric<br>
Travelers of Norrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=numnayan>Numnayan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 2521<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(12/2/03 11:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3716.topic&index=178>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.hneguild.com/Num/numbounceevil2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> They work hard for their money<br>
