<br>
1. The BF has been weak lately.  The occasional clueless newcomer wanders in to complain about something so lame that it barely distracts the denizens from their default passtime of fucking Rthen's corpse.  An actual flame = fresh meat, and something for Nandarie to do besides testing out new kinds of lube for getting his head ever further up his ass.<br>
<br>
2. ToN has been a bit too successful for its own good.  We raid pretty much every night, we start earlier than other U.S. guilds, and we keep track of what other folks have killed so we don't waste time.  Seems clear from the tone of this thread that we haven't made ourselves more popular by taking more than our &quot;share&quot; of the available mobs.<br>
<br>
Boo hoo.<br>
<br>
Frankly, its funny to see all the pissing and moaning coming from some of you, specifically those of you whose guild is disintegrating under the accumulated weight of years of bad karma.  As for some others:<br>
<br>
Ainian: just where in this thread does anyone say that we didn't benefit from the knowledge that our HnE recruits brought us?  Simply calling us hypocrites doesn't make it so, you need to be able to point to where we actually said the thing you are yelling about from on top of that high horse.<br>
<br>
Kordin: Glass houses and stones, etc..  Start returning the consideration we show you by not moving on planes where you are already raiding and lagging you out, then you may have some grounds to complain about anything we do.<br>
<br>
As for the whole stupid argument about strats, cheating and who is more or less worthy to bop virtual bippies - the real root of our success and progression over the past 15 months has to do with great leadership and hard work.  The single greatest thing we've accomplished is to build a guild from the scraps Laurri left behind and to keep it together.  Where we got our info on beating various encounters is truly beside the point in the face of that.  Bottom line, ToN is a great guild, I'm damn proud to be a member, and the distant whining sound issuing from the BF whenever we take another step forward just gives me a warm feeling in my special place. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=366694">Nayl</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
